HEADWORD: Sulphotungstic
<hw>Sul`pho*tung"stic</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of, pertaining to, or designating, hypothetical
sulphacid of tungsten (called also <xex>sulphowolframic acid</xex>),
analogous to sulphuric acid, and known in its salts.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sulphovinic</ent>⟦br⟧
